songs.title: Let Go

description.plain:
At just 17-years-old, Houston rapper Aaron May sounds wise beyond his years. His voice is smokey yet rich with melody as he raps about wanting something real from his girl on the new single “Let Go.” The track is self-produced and uses a beautiful soul sample as added depth. May goes into depth about wearing his “heart on my sleeve ‘til it’s left on the curb,” and nodding to his tender years when he says, “if I ain’t your man, I don’t want no hickey.”

When asked to him about what the song means to him, he said, “I’ve been in some situations where I was holding on to someone that was doing me no good and at some point, you get tired of dealing with certain B.S., that’s when you let go.”

songs.title: I’m Good Luv, Enjoy.

description.plain: The title of the song is most likely referring to an infamous text that Future made to Instagram model Shamartess Whitsett. The two of them talked on and off for a while and Future wanted to see her. She wanted Future to pay for the flight but Future told her that he would pay for the flight once she made it there. Once she arrived… she realized Future wanted a more sexual encounter and even booked a Hotel for a night. She denies the sex which leads Future to just leave her in Los Angeles before this infamous reply

songs.title: Make It

description.plain:
“Make It” is the intro to Aaron May’s first debut album released February 28, 2019.

The song serves as a message to the listeners that he has high hopes for their futures and growth as people.

The song may have also been a self note to his future self, as he was only 17 years old at the time of the album’s release.
